    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1975-06-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1975-06-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="288"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d288">
                <head>288. National Security Decision Memorandum 298<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d288fn1">
                        <p>
                            <seg type="summary">Summary: The President directed that a <gloss
                                    target="#t_COCOM_1">COCOM</gloss> exemption be granted to allow
                                the sale of a <gloss target="#t_FRG_1">FRG</gloss> nuclear reactor
                                to the <gloss target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss>, provided certain
                                safeguard measures were met.</seg>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <seg type="source">Source: Ford Library, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1"
                                    >NSC</gloss> Institutional Files (H-Files), Box 60, <gloss
                                    target="#t_NSDM_1">NSDM</gloss> 298—<gloss target="#t_FRG_1"
                                    >FRG</gloss> Reactor Sale to the <gloss target="#t_USSR_1"
                                    >USSR</gloss>. Secret. Copy sent to the <gloss target="#t_DCI_1"
                                    >DCI</gloss>.</seg>
                        </p>
                    </note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1975-06-14">June 14, 1975</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="to">
                    <head>TO</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of Defense</item>
                    <item>The Deputy Secretary of State</item>
                    <item>The Director, Arms Control and Disarmament Agency</item>
                    <item>The Administrator, Energy Research and Development Administration</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_FRG_1">FRG</gloss> Reactor Sale to the <gloss
                            target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>The President has reviewed the paper prepared by the <gloss target="#t_NSC_1"
                        >NSC</gloss> Verification Panel Working Group on the above subject, and has
                    noted the views of the addressees. He has decided that:</p>
                <p>—The U.S. is prepared to grant an exemption for the <gloss target="#t_FRG_1"
                        >FRG</gloss> reactor sale now pending before <gloss target="#t_COCOM_1"
                        >COCOM</gloss> if the <gloss target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss> will supply the
                    uranium for the fuel and give a peaceful purposes assurance for the reactor and
                    its produced plutonium.</p>
                <p>—<gloss target="#t_IAEA_1">IAEA</gloss> safeguards should be required in future
                        <gloss target="#t_COCOM_1">COCOM</gloss> cases for weapon states only where
                    the nuclear export concerned would reasonably be expected to create a
                    significant risk of diversion of fissionable materials to non-peaceful uses.</p>
                <pb facs="0931" n="889" type="typeset" xml:id="pg_889"/>
                <p>The President has also directed that the working group prepare a study of the
                    prospects and implications of U.S. nuclear trade with Communist countries, with
                    a view to reconciling our national and <gloss target="#t_COCOM_1">COCOM</gloss>
                    positions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed corresp="#p_KH_1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KH_1">Henry A. Kissinger</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
